-- CTC Media’s CTC TV Audience Drops in Russia, TNS-Global Says
-- B y   H a l i a   P a v l i v a
-- 2012-08-09T20:08:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-09/ctc-media-s-ctc-tv-audience-drops-in-russia-tns-global-says.html
CTC Media Inc. (CTCM) ’s CTC television
channel saw its average daily share of Russian viewers aged 4
years and older retreat in the week to Aug. 5, according to TNS-
Global.  Viewer share for CTC TV, the Nasdaq-listed Russian media
company’s biggest source of revenue, fell to 5.4 percent in the
week to Aug. 5 from 5.8 percent a week earlier, data researcher
TNS-Global said by e-mail today. CTC fell to seventh most-
watched TV channel in the country in the week to Aug. 5, as
Rossiya-2 and Fifth Channel gained viewer share, the data show.  CTC’s average daily audience among viewers 18 years old and
over fell to 5 percent from 5.2, the data show. CTC declined to
eight place from seventh in that viewer category, TNS-Global
said.  Russia’s NTV Television, Rossiya-1 and Pervyi Kanal were
the top three most watched in both categories. TNT TV, Rossiya-2
and Fifth Channel placed ahead of CTC among viewers 4 years and
older, the data show. Rossiya-2, TNT TV, Fifth Channel and REN
TV outpaced CTC among viewers 18 years and older in the week to
Aug. 5, the data showed.  To contact the reporters on this story:
